{"questionId":"9074720","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Two capacitors C<sub>1</sub> and C<sub>2</sub> of capacitance 28 µF and 22 µF respectively are connected in&nbsp;a circuit with a two-way switch and a cell of emf 1.5 V with a negligible internal resistance.&nbsp;The capacitors are initially uncharged. The switch is then connected to position A.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/8c000573f10c398e7a970a2f63888732450f755d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The switch is moved to position B.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the energy transferred from capacitor C<sub>1</sub>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>i</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>28</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;«J»&nbsp; ✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>total capacitance = 50 «μF»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>pd =&nbsp;«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>42</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>50</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>»&nbsp;0.84 «V»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>charge on C<sub>1</sub> after switch moved to B = 0.0235 «mC» ✓</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>E</mi><mtext>f</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>28</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>84</mn></mrow><